New Expected Completion Date of the Program of Study

description: Change Expected Program Completion Date Event Data

validation.validation: Enter a declared program of study for the student.

You can't change the expected program completion date for a student's program of study when any of these events are in progress: Add, Change, Make Primary, or Remove Program of Study, Change Expected Program Completion Date, Institutional Withdrawal, Leave of Absence, and Conferral Request.
The new completion date must be after the student's declare date for this program of study.
Submit either Student Reference or Academic Record Reference.

The student has received a waiver for an academic period that is on a different calendar than the calendar of the program for which you are attempting to change the expected completion date. To change the expected completion date,  adjust the waiver to $0.

The student has disbursed awards or disbursed sponsor contract for an academic period that is on a different calendar than the calendar of the program for which you are attempting to change the expected completion date. To change the expected completion date, adjust the disbursed award or disbursed sponsor contract to $0.
Specify an Academic Record Reference. If you're using a version before v30.0 of the web service operation, update to the latest version.
